Position the person on his or her back. If there are no injuries and the person is breathing, raise the person's legs above heart level — about 12 inches (30 centimeters) — if possible. Loosen belts, collars or other constrictive clothing.don't get the person up too quickly. If the person doesn't regain consciousness within one minute, call 190.If the person isn't breathing, begin CPR. Call 190. Continue CPR until help arrives or the person begins to breathe.If the person was injured in a fall associated with a faint, treat bumps, bruises or cuts appropriately. Control bleeding with direct pressure.